{
  "stem": "12768.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 82,
      "text": "And I thought many times it would be nicer to go out skiing instead of going in there on Sunday and going to religious teaching, you know.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 83,
      "text": "And so we never had this pressure, you could say, with knowing you were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 84,
      "text": "I knew only from in school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 85,
      "text": "I didn't attend the religious hour that they had.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 86,
      "text": "So that day, I could go and play or do whatever I wanted.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 87,
      "text": "And I thought that was neat, you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 88,
      "text": "And so nobody ever really bothered us, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 89,
      "text": "And so you, you never thought about the difference.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I can tell you in relation to this that when I came to the United States, there was so many that asked me, what are you?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I said, well, I'm Danish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they said, well, Danish like-- then what is the religion in Denmark?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Oh, I said, the main religion is Lutheran.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Oh, oh.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then they turned around.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They they kind of asked, are you Lutheran?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I said, no, I'm Jewish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Oh, that was what we asked in the first place.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I said, why?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because I had never been asked in Denmark.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So I thought it was funny that I should asked here.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But of course, here things were changing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But-- so everything was going real great in Denmark.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Like I say, I attended   my work.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when I had my vacation, I went up to our summer place.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I enjoyed all the company of friends and relatives and whatever you have.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so I can only say at, at that point, we, we lived a pretty  good life until it was September, exactly the 30th of September 1943.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had, of course, a new rabbi, Marcus Melchior, which was the assistant rabbi.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
